<h1 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-1.InternalGateway">1.&nbsp;Internal Gateway=
</h1>
<h2 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-1.APIProxies:">1.&nbsp;API Proxies:</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.a:APIproxywithRemoteHostconfig"=
>Scenario 1.1.a : API proxy with Remote Host config</h3>
<p>If you are configuring a backendService and need to specify / override R=
emote Host settings you can do so by adding remoteHost.</p>
<p>You can enable&nbsp;allowHTTP11 and/or set&nbsp;transactionTimeout as pe=
r the example below.</p>
<p><strong>Important note</strong>: if another proxy is configuring the sam=
e parameters with different settings it will override the configurations, s=
o make sure to check for existing remote hosts if you are unsure.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>env/default/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---
backendService:
  hostname: externalproviderurl
  destinationNetwork: external
  remoteHost:
    allowHTTP11: true
    transactionTimeout: 60000
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.1:APIproxyinvokingaBasicAuthent=
icationbackend(usuallyaWDPAPIusingAPIKey&amp;Secret)">Scenario 1.1.1 : API =
proxy invoking a Basic Authentication backend (usually a WDP API using API =
Key &amp; Secret)</h3>
<p>For the proxy&nbsp;that is invoking the WDP API with&nbsp;base path as '=
/layer/domain/subdomain/version'&nbsp;will configure the endpoint&nbsp;of t=
he same gateway and endpoint -</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>env/default/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 basePath: /layer/domain/subdomain/version
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>env/&lt;env&gt;/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 scheme: https
 host: gw.eng1.api.srv.westpac.com.au
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>proxy-secret.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
authenticationProfiles: =20
 securityType: HTTP BASIC
 username: &lt;apiKey for WDP API&gt;
 password: &lt;apiSecret for WDP API&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Note : Westpac Root CA Cert will be used to perform the TLS</p>
<p>Reference Implementation -&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https=
://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-=
integ-ref-apiproxy-v1-api/browse" style=3D"text-decoration: none;text-align=
: left;" title=3D"wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-apiproxy-v1-api" rel=3D=
"nofollow">wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-apiproxy-v1-api</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.2:APIproxyinvokingaproviderendp=
ointwithHTTPBasicusingusername&amp;password">Scenario 1.1.2 : API proxy inv=
oking a provider endpoint&nbsp; with HTTP Basic using username &amp; passwo=
rd</h3>
<p>Endpoint is&nbsp;'<a rel=3D"nofollow">https://providerurl:50270'</a>&nbs=
p;and base path is /provider/base/path using Basic Authentication with user=
name as 'testUsername' and password as 'testPassword'.&nbsp;For Westpac Int=
ernal Provider system,&nbsp;Westpac Root CA Cert will be used to perform th=
e TLS and pipeline will take care of updating it while for external systems=
 you can update it as&nbsp;publicCert.pem</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 457.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 467.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Westpac Internal Endpoint config for env/default=
/proxy.yaml</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Westpac External Endpoint config for env/default=
/proxy.yaml</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>---</p><p>backendService:</p><p>&nbsp; basePa=
th: /provider/base/path</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>---</p><p>backendService:</p><p>&nbsp; basePa=
th: /provider/base/path</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;certificate: publicCert.pem</p><p=
>&nbsp;&nbsp;destinationNetwork: external</p><p>outboundRoutingPolicy: <spa=
n style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" dat=
a-ref=3D"180f4ecb-492f-43e1-afbf-36637af9d082">INTERNAL_INTERNET_PROXY_OUTB=
OUND_WITH_BASIC_AUTH_V2.0</span></span></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>/env/&lt;env&gt;/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 scheme: https
 hostname: providerurl
 port: 50270
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>proxy-secret.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
authenticationProfiles: =20
 securityType: HTTP BASIC
 username: testUsername
 password: testPassword</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Reference implementation -&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https=
://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-=
integ-ref-apiproxy-v1-api/browse" style=3D"text-decoration: none;text-align=
: left;" title=3D"wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-apiproxy-v1-api" rel=3D=
"nofollow">wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-apiproxy-v1-api</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.3:APIproxyinvokingaproviderendp=
ointwhichusesBasicAuthenticationalongwithSSLMutualAuthentication(HTTPBasic&=
amp;TLSMA)">Scenario 1.1.3 : API proxy invoking a provider endpoint which u=
ses Basic Authentication along with SSL Mutual Authentication (HTTP Basic &=
amp; TLS MA)</h3>
<p>Endpoint is&nbsp;'<a rel=3D"nofollow">https://providerurl:50270'</a>&nbs=
p;and base path is /provider/base/path will need the mutual authentication =
using key authkey.pfx&nbsp;and password for key file is&nbsp;'testPassword'=
. Also the rest api need to connect to provider using Basic Authentication =
with username as 'test_username' and password is 'test_password'.</p>
<p>Make sure the authkey.pfx is encrypted and&nbsp;checked into the same fo=
lder as that of proxy-secret.yaml</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 84.=
7317%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 40.5754%;">
<col style=3D"width: 59.3254%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Westpac Internal Endpoint config for env/default=
/proxy.yaml</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Westpac External Endpoint config for env/default=
/proxy.yaml</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>---</p><p>backendService:</p><p>&nbsp; basePa=
th: /provider/base/path</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>---</p><p>backendService:</p><p>&nbsp; basePa=
th: /provider/base/path</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;destinationNetwork: external</p><=
p>outboundRoutingPolicy: INTERNAL_INTERNET_PROXY_OUTBOUND_TLSMA_V1.0</p></t=
d>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>/env/&lt;env&gt;/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 scheme: https
 hostname: providerurl
 port: 50270</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>proxy-secret.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
authenticationProfiles: =20
 securityType: SSL
 pfx/p12file: authkey.pfx=20
 password: testPassword
 trustAll: True
outboundRequest:
 policy: OUTBOUND_BASIC_AUTH_V1.0
 username: test_username
 password: test_password</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Reference Implementation -&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https=
://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-=
integ-ref-apitlsmaproxy-v1-api/browse" style=3D"text-decoration: none;text-=
align: left;" title=3D"wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-apitlsmaproxy-v1-a=
pi" rel=3D"nofollow">wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-apitlsmaproxy-v1-api=
</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.4:APIproxyinvokinganproviderend=
pointthatrequiresTLSMutualAuthentication(TLSMA)">Scenario 1.1.4 : API proxy=
 invoking an provider endpoint that requires TLS Mutual Authentication (TLS=
 MA)</h3>
<p>Endpoint is&nbsp;'<a rel=3D"nofollow">https://providerurl:50270'</a>&nbs=
p;and base path is /provider/base/path will need the mutual authentication =
using key authkey.pfx&nbsp;and password for key file is&nbsp;'testPassword'=
.</p>
<p>Make sure the authkey.pfx is encrypted and&nbsp;checked into the same fo=
lder as that of proxy-secret.yaml</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 84.=
7317%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 40.5754%;">
<col style=3D"width: 59.3254%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Westpac Internal Endpoint config for env/default=
/proxy.yaml</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Westpac External Endpoint config for env/default=
/proxy.yaml</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>---</p><p>backendService:</p><p>&nbsp; basePa=
th: /provider/base/path</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>---</p><p>backendService:</p><p>&nbsp; basePa=
th: /provider/base/path</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;destinationNetwork: external</p><=
p>outboundRoutingPolicy: INTERNAL_INTERNET_PROXY_OUTBOUND_TLSMA_V1.0</p></t=
d>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>/env/&lt;env&gt;/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 scheme: https
 hostname: providerurl
 port: 50270
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>proxy-secret.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
authenticationProfiles: =20
 securityType: SSL
 pfx/p12file: authkey.pfx=20
 password: testPassword
 trustAll: True</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.5:APIproxyinvokingantokenandser=
viceendpointexternaltoWestpacviaInternetProxythatrequiresOAuth2(OAuth2)">Sc=
enario 1.1.5 : API proxy invoking an token and service endpoint external to=
 Westpac via Internet Proxy that requires OAuth2 (OAuth2)</h3>
<p>Endpoint is&nbsp;'<a rel=3D"nofollow">https://externalproviderurl:50270'=
</a>&nbsp;and base path is /provider/base/path will need the access token w=
hich is retrieved <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"f3d6175=
4-65be-4f14-ae54-c5db16ecb526">form</span> the provider authorization token=
 service using the tokenURL, client_id, client_secret, grant_type, scope.</=
p>
<p>This will need the routing policy to be configured to route to the inter=
net via Internet Proxy.&nbsp;This policy will also cache the token based on=
 the expires_in from response and will use the token in subsequent response=
 if not already expired.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>env/default/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 basePath: /provider/base/path
outboundRoutingPolicy: INTERNAL_INTERNET_PROXY_OUTBOUND_V2.0</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>/env/&lt;env&gt;/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 scheme: https
 hostname: externalproviderurl
 port: 50270
 certificate: publicCert.pem
 destinationNetwork: external</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>proxy-secret.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
outboundRequest:
 policy: OUTBOUND_API_OAUTH_V1.0
 tokenURL: https://auth_hostname:port/authtoken
 OAuth_type: Client_Credentials_In_Body
 client_id: test_client_id
 client_secret: test_client_secret
 grant_type: test_grant_type
 scope: test_scope</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluen=
ce-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Below sample is the oauth token service request in case of 'Client Crede=
ntials in Body'. The client_id, client_secret, grant_type and scope will be=
 present in the message body.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: powershell; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">P=
OST /oauth-service/auth/token HTTP/1.1
Host: oauth-hostname.com
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
client_id=3Dtes_client_id&amp;client_secret=3Dtest_client_secret&amp;grant_=
type=3Dtest_grant_type&amp;scope=3Dtest_scope
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>Below sample is the oauth token service request in case of 'Client Crede=
ntials in Header'. The client_id, client_secret will be part of the Authori=
zation Header with Base64 encoded value. The grant_type and scope will be p=
resent in the message body.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: powershell; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">P=
OST /oauth-service/auth/token HTTP/1.1
Host: oauth-hostname.com
Authorization: Basic dGVzdF9jbGllbnRfaWQ6dGVzdF9jbGllbnRfc2VjcmV0
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=3Dclient_credentials&amp;scope=3Daupr</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Sample response from the token service will be like -</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: powershell; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
    "access_token": "eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiItesttpZCI6ImVwdFlPZ21nZ0RiUVhmRHMiL=
CJwaS5hdG0iOiIzbjV3In0.eyJzY29wZSI6ImNvbnNlbnRfbWFpbnRhaW4gb3BlbmlkIiwiY2xp=
ZW50X2lkIjoid2RwYXBpX2NvbnNlbnQiLCJpc3MiOiJodHRwczovL2lkcC5wcmVwcm9kLndlc3R=
wYWMuY29tLmF1L2RldjEvaWRlbnRpdHkiLCJleHAiOjE1Njg2OTYxNDl9.T2pQbVjvbgo4rT8Bk=
p7Y7YFurLBjIUzJ3LrGoqqs0dWNgIRo3jwaUM24mKs_M1kUfw9VCMBETAcadSPwwiba3NY2VaUT=
urdkYibH6wJqjMvnQXtZJho4d3HbRhBbjzMeGm-dW6jvXkEVA87Db70MGGJIQbZOxERrIiBdWQN=
je8Tw_C8-YSsy7ZTNT3KgE-OXNg0FnUpnMuRQ0VVdWrdRLp009_b0FRYb9y7Tsj95Nz2QHr_xv8=
WF003uhAlgRRioBDzRzEWjii6jKgUN_IZWU4UdGBbbszJ4seH9yhP7J16PifyaTktnDEIiXOHgv=
mTsLPRBpzuvJRmmQawjNTkO0Q",
    "token_type": "Bearer",
    "expires_in": 299
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluen=
ce-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>The OUTBOUND_API_OAUTH_V1.0 policy will refresh the token every 60s or i=
f the expiry time is within 10s. This means that it is not appropriate for =
use with backends where the authorization call is very slow or expensive.</=
p>
</div>
</div>
<h4 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.5.1:Respectingtheexpires_invalu=
eofthetoken">Scenario 1.1.5.1: Respecting the expires_in value of the token=
</h4>
<p>For use cases where it is important to response the expires_in value of =
the token, for example use cases where the auth call is very slow or expens=
ive a newer version of the policy is available.</p>
<p>Specifying the OUTBOUND_API_OAUTH_V1.1 will instruct the gateway to resp=
ect the token expiry and will not attempt to renew the token every 60s. All=
 inputs are the same as described in Scenario 1.1.5</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>proxy-secret.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
outboundRequest:
 policy: OUTBOUND_API_OAUTH_V1.1
 tokenURL: https://auth_hostname:port/authtoken
 OAuth_type: Client_Credentials_In_Body
 client_id: test_client_id
 client_secret: test_client_secret
 grant_type: test_grant_type
 scope: test_scope</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-i=
nformation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>It is important to be aware of how the backend service is going to suppo=
rt authentication.</p>
<p>In the cases where the backend enforcement point is querying the IDP to =
find out&nbsp; if a token is valid then if the IDP invalidates the token th=
ere will be an outage until the tokens expire.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.6:APIproxyusingX-AuthorizationH=
eaderfornon-standardAuthentication">Scenario 1.1.6 : API proxy using X-Auth=
orization Header for non-standard Authentication</h3>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-war=
ning"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-=
information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p><span data-teams=3D"true">Non-standard authentication patterns should un=
dergo security architecture review.&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p>Endpoint is&nbsp;'<a rel=3D"nofollow">https://providerurl:50270'</a>&nbs=
p;and base path is /provider/base/path using X-Authorization header copied =
to Authorization header in order to authenticate the provider.&nbsp;</p>
<p>This provides a means to support a non-st<span data-teams=3D"true">andar=
d or obsolete authentication scheme and still leverage the remaining proxy =
controls, for examples Custom authentication or OAuth 1.0.</span></p>
<p>Since it's assumed to be a Westpac Internal Provider system, the Westpac=
 Internal Root CA Cert will be used to perform the TLS and the pipeline wil=
l take care of updating it.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>env/default/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 basePath: /provider/base/path
outboundRequestPolicy: OUTBOUND_ADD_AUTHORIZATION_V1.0
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>/env/&lt;env&gt;/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 scheme: https
 hostname: providerurl
 port: 50270</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Reference Implementation -&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https=
://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-=
integ-ref-apiaddauthproxy-v1-api/browse" style=3D"text-decoration: none;tex=
t-align: left;" title=3D"wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-apiaddauthproxy-=
v1-api" rel=3D"nofollow">wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-apiaddauthproxy-=
v1-api</a></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluen=
ce-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>If you are invoking a system external to Westpac, then you can add the r=
outing configuration 'outboundRoutingPolicy: INTERNAL_INTERNET_PROXY_OUTBOU=
ND_V2.0' in your proxy.yaml along with above.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.7:APIproxyinvokinganendpointint=
ernaltoWestpacthatrequiresOAuth2PasswordGrant(OAuth2)">Scenario 1.1.7 : API=
 proxy invoking an endpoint internal to Westpac that requires OAuth2 Passwo=
rd Grant(OAuth2)</h3>
<p>Endpoint is&nbsp;'<a rel=3D"nofollow">https://providerurl:50270'</a>&nbs=
p;and base path is /provider/base/path will need the access token which is =
retrieved form the provider authorization token service using the tokenURL,=
 username, password, grant_type.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>env/default/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 basePath: /provider/base/path</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>/env/&lt;env&gt;/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 scheme: https
 hostname: providerurl
 port: 50270
# extra parameters are optional (Not applicable for most of the cases)
extraParameters:
    format: json
    resources: a00123</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>proxy-secret.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
outboundRequest:
 policy: OUTBOUND_API_OAUTH_PASSWORD_GRANT_V1.0
 tokenURL: https://auth_hostname:port/authtoken
 client_id: test_username
 client_secret: test_password
 grant_type: test_grant_type</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluen=
ce-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Below sample is the oauth token service request in case of 'Client Crede=
ntials in Body'. The client_id, client_secret, grant_type and scope will be=
 present in the message body.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: powershell; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">P=
OST /oauth-service/auth/token HTTP/1.1
Host: oauth-hostname.com
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
username=3Dtest_username&amp;password=3Dtest_password&amp;grant_type=3Dtest=
_grant_type&amp;format=3Djson&amp;resources=3Da00123
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Token Response will be in below format -</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluen=
ce-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>{<br>
 "token_type": "bearer",<br>
 "access_token": "test_testAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzUxMiJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJhbGZhY=
mV0IiwiaWF0IjoiMTU2MDI0OTcwOCIsImV4cCI6IjE1NjA4NDk2NDgiLCJxc2giOm51bGwsInN1=
YiI6IkFwaSBBdXRoZW50aWNhdGlvbiIsImNvbnRleHQiOnsidXNlciI6eyJVc2VyS2V5IjoiVEV=
TVEFQSSIsIlVzZXJuYW1lIjoiVEVTVEFQSSIsIkRpc3BsYXlOYW1lIjoiQVBJIiwiU2Vzc2lvbi=
I6IkY4ODhBOTlCOTc0MzRDMEM4QTFGQjhCN0FBQjAwMTRGIiwiQWNjZXNzVHlwZSI6MH19fQ.b6=
E1AZJxMtykv8XPVu_rwWIDMGdy2efEPe-CKms-__ZRmy6aQE8nZtestky6kCWtr8ogqA1qknsXR=
rrLNHIzLA"<br>
 }</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.8:APIproxyinvokingtokenandservi=
ceendpointinternaltoWestpacthatrequiresOAuth2withmultiplescopes(OAuth2)">Sc=
enario 1.1.8 : API proxy invoking token and service endpoint internal to We=
stpac that requires OAuth2 with multiple scopes (OAuth2)</h3>
<p>Endpoint is&nbsp;'<a rel=3D"nofollow">https://providerurl:50270'</a>&nbs=
p;and base path is /provider/base/path will need the access token which is =
retrieved form the provider authorization token service using the tokenURL,=
 client_id, client_secret, grant_type, scopes.</p>
<p>This policy will also cache the token based on the expires_in from respo=
nse and will use the token in subsequent response if not already expired.</=
p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>env/default/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 basePath: /provider/base/path</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>/env/&lt;env&gt;/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 scheme: https
 hostname: providerurl
 port: 50270
 certificate: publicCert.pem
# extra parameters are optional (Not applicable for most of the cases)
extraParameters:
 format: json
 resources: a00123</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>proxy-secret.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
outboundRequest:
 policy: OUTBOUND_API_OAUTH_V2.0
 tokenURL: https://auth_hostname:port/authtoken
 OAuth_type: Client_Credentials_In_Body
 client_id: test_client_id
 client_secret: test_client_secret
 grant_type: test_grant_type
 scope: test_scope1 test_scope2</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Below sample is the oauth token service request in case of 'Client Crede=
ntials in Body'. The client_id, client_secret, grant_type and scope will be=
 present in the message body.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: powershell; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">P=
OST /oauth-service/auth/token HTTP/1.1
Host: oauth-hostname.com
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
client_id=3Dtes_client_id&amp;client_secret=3Dtest_client_secret&amp;grant_=
type=3Dtest_grant_type&amp;scope=3Dtest_scope1%20test_scope2&amp;format=3Dj=
son&amp;resources=3Da00123</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Sample response from the token service will be like -</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: powershell; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
    "access_token": "eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiItesttpZCI6ImVwdFlPZ21nZ0RiUVhmRHMiL=
CJwaS5hdG0iOiIzbjV3In0.eyJzY29wZSI6ImNvbnNlbnRfbWFpbnRhaW4gb3BlbmlkIiwiY2xp=
ZW50X2lkIjoid2RwYXBpX2NvbnNlbnQiLCJpc3MiOiJodHRwczovL2lkcC5wcmVwcm9kLndlc3R=
wYWMuY29tLmF1L2RldjEvaWRlbnRpdHkiLCJleHAiOjE1Njg2OTYxNDl9.T2pQbVjvbgo4rT8Bk=
p7Y7YFurLBjIUzJ3LrGoqqs0dWNgIRo3jwaUM24mKs_M1kUfw9VCMBETAcadSPwwiba3NY2VaUT=
urdkYibH6wJqjMvnQXtZJho4d3HbRhBbjzMeGm-dW6jvXkEVA87Db70MGGJIQbZOxERrIiBdWQN=
je8Tw_C8-YSsy7ZTNT3KgE-OXNg0FnUpnMuRQ0VVdWrdRLp009_b0FRYb9y7Tsj95Nz2QHr_xv8=
WF003uhAlgRRioBDzRzEWjii6jKgUN_IZWU4UdGBbbszJ4seH9yhP7J16PifyaTktnDEIiXOHgv=
mTsLPRBpzuvJRmmQawjNTkO0Q",
    "token_type": "Bearer",
    "expires_in": 299
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluen=
ce-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>The OUTBOUND_API_OAUTH_V2.0 policy will refresh the token every 60s or i=
f the expiry time is within 10s. This means that it is not appropriate for =
use with backends where the authorization call is very slow or expensive.</=
p>
</div>
</div>
<h4 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.1.8.1:Respectingtheexpires_invalu=
eofthetoken">Scenario 1.1.8.1: Respecting the expires_in value of the token=
</h4>
<p>For use cases where it is important to response the expires_in value of =
the token, for example use cases where the auth call is very slow or expens=
ive a newer version of the policy is available.</p>
<p>Specifying the OUTBOUND_API_OAUTH_V2.1 will instruct the gateway to resp=
ect the token expiry and will not attempt to renew the token every 60s. All=
 inputs are the same as described in Scenario 1.1.5</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>proxy-secret.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
outboundRequest:
 policy: OUTBOUND_API_OAUTH_V2.1
 tokenURL: https://auth_hostname:port/authtoken
 OAuth_type: Client_Credentials_In_Body
 client_id: test_client_id
 client_secret: test_client_secret
 grant_type: test_grant_type
 scope: test_scope</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-i=
nformation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>It is important to be aware of how the backend service is going to suppo=
rt authentication.</p>
<p>In the cases where the backend enforcement point is querying the IDP to =
find out&nbsp; if a token is valid then if the IDP invalidates the token th=
ere will be an outage until the tokens expire.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-2.WSDLProxies:">2. WSDL Proxies:</h2>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<p class=3D"title conf-macro-render">Inbound Security for Web Services</p><=
span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informat=
ion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>For Web Service Proxies the inbound security will always be Password Dig=
est Authentication which will use api key and api secret as the username an=
d password to generate the ws-security username token</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Proxyusecasescenarios-Scenario1.2.1:WebServiceProxyinvokingawebse=
rvicethatrequirePasswordDigestasInboundSecurityandPasswordDigestalongwithSS=
Lasoutboundsecurity(Passworddigest&amp;TLS)"><br>
 Scenario&nbsp;1.2.1 : Web Service Proxy invoking a&nbsp; web service that =
require Password Digest as Inbound Security and Password Digest along with =
SSL as outbound security (Password digest &amp; TLS)</h3>
<p>Endpoint external to Westpac as&nbsp;'<a rel=3D"nofollow">https://extern=
alproviderurl:50270'</a>&nbsp;and base path is /provider/base/path will nee=
d the TLS using 'publicCert.pem' Also the web service need to connect to pr=
ovider using Username Token (Password Digest) username as 'test_username' a=
nd password is 'test_password'.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Westpac Internal Endpoint config for env/default=
/proxy.yaml</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Westpac External Endpoint config for env/default=
/proxy.yaml</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>---</p><p>backendService:</p><p>&nbsp; basePa=
th: /provider/base/path</p><p>inboundSecurityPolicy: INBOUND_WS_AUTH_PASSWO=
RD_DIGEST_V1.0</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>---</p><p>backendService:</p><p>&nbsp; basePa=
th: /provider/base/path</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;destinationNetwork: external</p><=
p>inboundSecurityPolicy: INBOUND_WS_AUTH_PASSWORD_DIGEST_V1.0</p><p>outboun=
dRoutingPolicy: INTERNAL_INTERNET_PROXY_OUTBOUND_V2.0</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>/env/&lt;env&gt;/proxy.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
backendService:
 scheme: https
 hostname: externalproviderurl
 port: 50270
 destinationNetwork: external</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>proxy-secret.yaml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---=20
outboundRequest:
 policy: OUTBOUND_WS_AUTH_PASSWORD_DIGEST_V2.0=20
 username: test_username
 password: test_password</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p class=3D"diff-block-target diff-block-context">Reference Implementation =
using soap 1.1 -&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitbucket.=
srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-wsu=
