</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"2112698654">AppDynamics in Mesh Containers</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"6a22a337-d7b0-43d4-b1af-e99d65e7=
7ad4-2112698654">
<h1 id=3D"AppDynamicsinMeshContainers-Changes">Changes</h1>
<p>This section will keep track of requirements for running AppD in the Mes=
h.</p>
<p><strong>28/08/2025 -<br></strong>The following container profiles no lon=
ger officially support AppDynamics. They might work, however any validation=
 that AppDynamics continues to function will be the responsibility of proje=
cts.<br>
 They will not intentionally receive AppDynamics security patches.</p>
<ul>
<li>Javaweb 1</li>
<li>Springboot 1</li>
<li>Node 14</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"AppDynamicsinMeshContainers-Pre-Requisites">Pre-Requisites</h1>
<ol>
<li>As described in the "Onboarding to AppD" section, your mesh domain shou=
ld already be onboarded. If you find that one is not please let us know.</l=
i>
</ol>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-i=
nformation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p><strong>For nodejs containers only</strong></p>
<p>Make sure that your build artifact produces a file build/api/index.js</p=
>
<p>You can tell if this is working correctly by looking in splunk for the s=
tartup.log file, if a log message like "<span><span class=3D"ui-provider cu=
r cus c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t cut cuu w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah=
 ai aj ak">Could not find build/api/index.js file, launching node via npm. =
This is a BAD thing." exists then appd will <strong>not</strong> work.</spa=
n></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"AppDynamicsinMeshContainers-OnboardingtoAppD">Onboarding to AppD<=
/h1>
<p>For onboarding to appd see the Onboarding your API section of this page:=
</p>
<p><a href=3D"/display/SD/WDP+API+Monitoring+-+Onboarding+Framework">WDP AP=
I Monitoring - Onboarding Framework</a></p>
<p>Most domains should already have an application set up.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-i=
nformation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Any new applications <strong>must</strong> be included in the scope for =
license rule "WDP-A008E0"</p>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"AppDynamicsinMeshContainers-InputstogetAppDynamicsRunning">Inputs=
 to get AppDynamics Running</h1>
<h2 id=3D"AppDynamicsinMeshContainers-Overview">Overview</h2>
<p>AppDynamics is made available to specific API's that want to use it by p=
arsing a specifically named configuration file and ensuring all of the requ=
ired variables are available.&nbsp;</p>
<p>This appd-config.properties file must exist in any environment in which =
you would like to use AppDynamics (this should be all environments as the A=
ppDynamics Applications are created.</p>
<p>You must specify a single variable in the properties file:</p>
<p>APPDYNAMICS_AGENT_APPLICATION_NAME</p>
<h3 id=3D"AppDynamicsinMeshContainers-appd-config.properties">appd-config.p=
roperties</h3>
<p>This file is unencrypted and placed in your environment directories, for=
 example <code>env/dev1/appd-config.properties</code></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>appd-config.properties</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">APPDYNAMICS=
_AGENT_APPLICATION_NAME=3D&lt;The AppD Agent Application Name&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>For example, during testing this was the properties file which we used:<=
/p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>appd-config.properties</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">APPDYNAMICS=
_AGENT_APPLICATION_NAME=3DWDP-A008E0-DEV</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"AppDynamicsinMeshContainers-BehaviourstobeAwareof">Behaviours to =
be Aware of</h1>
<ol>
<li>:warning:&nbsp;When your container starts up with AppDynamics it will t=
ake a lot longer. If you test this on a laptop the difference is trivial, h=
owever in the heavily resource constrained containers APIs run in, this is =
notable.</li>
<li>Appd will be installed in your container as part of the build process i=
f there are appd configuration files available in the env directories.=20
<ol>
<li>This means that you will need to perform regular rebuilds of your compo=
nents to ensure you are using a patched version of the appd agent. Posts ar=
e made on Yammer when new versions are released.</li>
<li>This means that you cannot retrofit appd to an existing deployment that=
 has already been built. You need to build a new container so that appd get=
s installed.</li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
